Look up in allodb information about each equation_id.

allo_lookup.Rd

Look up in allodb information about each equation_id.

allo_lookup(data, allodb = allodb::equations)

Arguments

data

A dataframe with columns rowid and equation_id
allodb

A table from allodb.

Value

A dataframe.

See also

Other functions to manipulate equations: add_equations, allo_evaluate, allo_find

Examples

census <- fgeo.biomass::scbi_tree1
species <- fgeo.biomass::scbi_species

best <- census %>%
  add_species(species, site = "scbi") %>%
  allo_find() %>%
  fixme_drop_duplicated_rowid()
#> `sp` now stores Latin species names
#> Joining, by = c("sp", "site")
#> Warning:   The input and output datasets have different number of rows:
#>   * Input: 40283.
#>   * Output: 30229.
#> Warning: Dropping 783 rows with duplicated `rowid` values.

ids <- add_equations(census, best)
#> Joining, by = "rowid"
allo_lookup(ids)
